<!DOCTYPE html> //used to state that we are working in HTML 5 
<html> // what is in between these brackets are considered html
  <head> // has information that isnt displayed on the website
    <title>Richard</title>
    <link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Playfair+Display:200|Raleway:100' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
  	<div class="container">
  		<h1>Richard</h1>
  	  <a class="btn" href="#">Get Started</a>
  	</div>
  </body>
</html> //html bracket


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Animals Around the World</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>The Brown Bear</h1> // this is the headings any other headings will be the subheading.
  <!-- A section that describes the brown bear -->
  <p>info about bears can be added here</p> //paragraph items.
  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brown_bear">Learn More</a> // works as a hyperlink 
  <p>Here are some bear species:</p>
  <ul> // creates an unordered lists
    <li>Arctos</li>
    <li>Collarus</li> // these make the bullet point lists.
    <li>Horribilis</li>
    <li>Nelsoni (extinct)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The following countries have the largest populations of brown bears:</p>
  <ol> //similar to an ordered list except each item is numbered.
    <li>Russia</li>
    <li>United States</li>
    <li>Canada</li>
  </ol>
  <a href="#" target="_blank">
    <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/codecademy-content/courses/web-101/web101-image_brownbear.jpg" /></a>
</body> 
</html>
